result.execSummary:
This case is being appealed. If the court makes a decision in a case that a party disagrees with, the party may have the right to seek review by a higher court to determine if the trial court's decision was correct. Appeals are most often made after a trial or final decision in a case, but an appeal can also occur before a final decision.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jose M Dancel in court with attorney Anthony D Cotton.  Defendant Jose M Dancel in custody.  
Denis John Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Denials set forth by defense as to information within the presentence investigation report.
Hearing proceeded.  Statements made by the state, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Ashley C. and Conchita D.

THE COURT ORDERS:
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 35 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to all other counts and any existing sentence with credit for 0 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 25 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 10 YEARS.

COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 12 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to all other counts and any existing sentence with credit for 0 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 8 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 4 YEARS.

COUNT 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to all other counts and any existing sentence with credit for 0 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

COUNT 4:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to all other counts and any existing sentence with credit for 0 days. 
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*No contact with victim Ashley C. or her family;
*Submit dna sample- surcharge WAIVED (due to previous payment of dna surcharge);
*Cooperate with any terms and conditions recommended by the Department of Corrections;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs;

The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  The Court ordered all financial obligations to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison wages and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.

Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms, body armor, or ammunition.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  
Defendant advised of his right to appeal this sentence.
